ear'd PvP class?</span><hr size=1> At low levels, and when facing people with no resists, then any caster has it easy. It becomes impossibly hard once your opponents start wearing resist gear, MR gear first, because that means you can't root them, and then simply FR/CR because it means your normal DD won't do much and you need to resort to the use of unresistable spells (lures in the case of wizards, winged death/splurt/blood lines etc for dots) <p>Aurore
<HR>
~Seekers of Divinity~
<BR>
Sorceress of 
<a href=http://www.ralloszek.net>Rallos Zek</a><BR>
<a href=http://www.progressquest.com><img src=http://www-rocq.inria.fr/~bnguyen/pony.gif></img></a>The Pony with the Pointy Hat.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uchifiir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chifiir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/02 5:41:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: So is a Wizard a fear'd PvP class?</span><hr size=1> No.<br>
<br>
Upper level players have zany resists<br>
Upper level players have crazy hps<br>
We have no hps.<br>
<br>
We are a &quot;Surprise!  You're dead!&quot; class, and then we run the hell away.  Gankers.<br>
<br>
Can we kill? Yeah.<br>
Can we gank?  Yeah.<br>
Are we feared?  No way.<br>
<br>
-Szii Uln'hyrr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/02 7:15:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> wiz pks</span><hr size=1> Wizards are good when they can get the drop on people sort of like rogues.<br>
<br>
So do you want to get kills or win duels.  I'd tend to think the former are more profitable than the latter.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uevantineessidel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evantine Essidel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://evantine.homestead.com/files/Eventine.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/02 11:04:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: wiz pks</span><hr size=1> There's so many factors to consider it's not even funny. Unsurprisingly, the better player makes the better PKer, without a shred of doubt, regardless of class. Skill is infinitly more important than every other factor that you could put into your character. I've killed monks twinked with fungi's and amazing 1hb weapons solo with my untwinked necro.<br>
<br>
If your looking for an easy answer, then the best PvP class in my mind is the shadowknight, who can heal himself and kill you with ease, followed closely by the monk.<br>
<br>
Level has everything to do with it, too. A wizard is deadly at 60, but is really not anything at 6. If your looking to make a PK character, make what you want to make, but just remember that you have to get to that grind sometime. You can't ONLY pvp. Choose a class that you want to play, not a class that you think is going to pwn everything. <p><center><img src="http://evantine.homestead.com/files/evantine.jpg"><br>
<font size=-3><a href="http://www.geocities.com/knightsofthesilvermoon/Evan.html">Storyline</a> | <a href="http://www.graffe.com">Graffe's Wizard Compilation</a> | <a href="http://www.iron-tower.com/">Iron Tower</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufrosthoundsz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FrosthoundSZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/6/02 4:57:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~scoventon/EQ/fh.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: wiz pks</span><hr size=1> I'm afraid of lures.  And manaburn (hello nerf).<br>
<br>
The answer is yes, wizards are feared, and they straight up own the score chart on Sullon Zek for a good reason. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvelaelsoulrender.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Velael Soulrender</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/9/02 10:49:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mmogamers.com/hate/ikonboard/avatars/joe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: wiz pks</span><hr size=1> A 60 wizard with SCF and SCFM is a thing to be feared. Dropping double damage lure of ice bombs on people has a habit of doing that.<br>
<br>
Before luclin, the answer to this question would be hell no, now, post-luclin and AA, I'd have to say a top-end wizard is quite a feared class. <p>Sorceror of <a href=http://www.mmogamers.com/hate>Hate</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utinthalastigris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tinthalas Tigris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/14/02 9:59:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: wiz pks</span><hr size=1> If you're looking to buy a car that will get you from here to there faster than you can zip up your fly, then you're going to have to know how to drive it.<br>
<br>
With that being said, someone driving a camaro stock with one hand on the wheel and both eyes forward at the stop light while a rocket of rice pulls up alongside lowered 6 inches below the ground with dubs and rads newly equipped with the latest Mars and Mystere CD in the system. - some would bet on the rocket. but little does rocketboy  know that under the hood of that camaro is a bored out 350,  worked up to a heavy 410 with increased oxygen intake, foot pressed a tenth of the way down on the gas pedal, and held full on the break to give it a steady idle and a rip of air as soon as the break gets lifted.<br>
<br>
Ask yourself, Who do *you* think is going to win? The one with too much pride, or the one with confidence who knows exactly what his car is capable of.<br>
<br>
-- To that degree, it doesn't matter if you're a twinked wizard. It all relates to whether or not you can use the items and spells you have. <br>
<br>
What the previous posters have stated, we're a fast acting &quot;ganking&quot; class. We strike hard fast, loot quick and get outta there yesterday.<br>
